==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Accoil
<hw>Ac*coil"</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧k*koil")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>acoillir</ets> to receive, F. <ets>accueillir</ets>; L.
<ets>ad</ets> + <ets>colligere</ets> to collect. See
<er>Coil</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To gather together; to
collect.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>To coil together.</def>
<rj><au>Ham. Nav. Encyc.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Accolade</ent>⟦br⟧
